```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Start] -->|User starts login process|> B(Process: Show login form)
    B -->|User enters email and password|> C(Process: Validate email and password)
    C -->|Email and password valid|> D[Decision: Check if user exists]
    D -->|User exists|> E(Process: Verify password)
    E -->|Password correct|> F[Decision: Login successful]
    F -->|Login successful|> G(Output: Login successful)
    F -->|Invalid password|> H(Process: Display error message)
    H -->|User tries to login again|> B
    D -->|User does not exist|> I(Process: Display error message)
    I -->|User wants to recover password|> J(Process: Send password recovery email)
    J -->|User enters new password|> K(Process: Update password)
    K -->|Password updated|> L[Decision: Password recovery successful]
    L -->|Password recovery successful|> G
    L -->|Invalid new password|> M(Process: Display error message)
    M -->|User tries to recover password again|> J
    C -->|Email and password invalid|> N(Process: Display error message)
    N -->|User wants to recover password|> J
    N -->|User wants to create new account|> O(Process: Redirect to registration page)
    O -->|User creates new account|> P[Decision: Registration successful]
    P -->|Registration successful|> G
    P -->|Registration failed|> Q(Process: Display error message)
    Q -->|User tries to register again|> O
    C -->|User wants to recover password|> J
    A -->|User starts over|> A
```